 LIBRARY AS LYCEUM.     THANKS TO GRANTS FROM THE NATIONAL ENDOWMENT FOR THE HUMANITIES (NEH), OHOOPEEREGIONAL LIBRARY IN VIDALIA, GEORGIA (POPULATION 11,200), ORGANISED 5PROGRAMMES IN 26 MONTHS. THEY WERE ABOUT THE OCCULT, DEATH, SCIENCE FICTION,THE NOBEL PRIZE, AND THE ART OF THE SHORT STORY, AND FEATURED VISITS FROMPROMINENT AUTHORS AND ACADEMICS. EXPLAINS HOW A SMALL PUBLIC LIBRARY SHOULDAPPLY FOR A NEH GRANT FOR PROGRAMMES; DESCRIBES HOW TO PLAN A PROGRAMME,APPROACH SPEAKERS, OBTAIN LOCAL FUNDING, AND MOUNT A PUBLICITY CAMPAIGN; ANDSTRESSES THE IMPORTANCE OF SUCH VENTURES IN SMALL COMMUNITIES WHERE THERE ISNO OTHER INSTITUTION TO OFFER THEM